  "transcript": {
    "language": "en",
    "is_generated": false,
    "segments": [
      {
        "start": 0.3,
        "duration": 1.9,
        "text": "- [David] Hello, wordsmiths,"
      },
      {
        "start": 2.1,
        "duration": 2.4,
        "text": "and greetings from an old sewer tunnel."
      },
      {
        "start": 4.6,
        "duration": 2.5,
        "text": "I'm doing a little bit of\nunderground exploration,"
      },
      {
        "start": 7.0,
        "duration": 2.0,
        "text": "which is really just a way of saying"
      },
      {
        "start": 9.1,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "I'm sneaking around\nwhere I ought not to be."
      },
      {
        "start": 11.2,
        "duration": 4.5,
        "text": "But look what I found\ndown here. (groaning)"
      },
      {
        "start": 15.8,
        "duration": 1.1,
        "text": "Words."
      },
      {
        "start": 16.8,
        "duration": 1.6,
        "text": "Wow, what a surprise."
      },
      {
        "start": 18.4,
        "duration": 2.6,
        "text": "But what's inside, oh ho?"
      },
      {
        "start": 22.0,
        "duration": 2.8,
        "text": "Accumulate, vast, and consist."
      },
      {
        "start": 24.8,
        "duration": 1.3,
        "text": "I'll define these words,"
      },
      {
        "start": 26.0,
        "duration": 1.6,
        "text": "I'll break 'em down into word parts,"
      },
      {
        "start": 27.6,
        "duration": 3.0,
        "text": "and then I'll use them in some sentences."
      },
      {
        "start": 30.6,
        "duration": 0.9,
        "text": "Let's get going."
      },
      {
        "start": 31.5,
        "duration": 3.0,
        "text": "Accumulate is a verb\nthat means to pile up,"
      },
      {
        "start": 34.5,
        "duration": 1.9,
        "text": "to increase in number."
      },
      {
        "start": 36.4,
        "duration": 3.9,
        "text": "Vast is an adjective that\nmeans very large or wide."
      },
      {
        "start": 40.3,
        "duration": 2.6,
        "text": "And consist is a verb that almost always"
      },
      {
        "start": 42.9,
        "duration": 2.5,
        "text": "is followed by the preposition of,"
      },
      {
        "start": 45.4,
        "duration": 2.8,
        "text": "and it means to be made from,"
      },
      {
        "start": 48.2,
        "duration": 1.9,
        "text": "like my band consists of me,"
      },
      {
        "start": 50.1,
        "duration": 2.6,
        "text": "Spatz Monroe, and Checky Valastro."
      },
      {
        "start": 52.8,
        "duration": 2.6,
        "text": "Those three people make up the band."
      },
      {
        "start": 55.4,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "The band consists of them."
      },
      {
        "start": 58.7,
        "duration": 2.1,
        "text": "Now, let's break these words down."
      },
      {
        "start": 60.8,
        "duration": 1.5,
        "text": "Accumulate is funny."
      },
      {
        "start": 62.3,
        "duration": 3.0,
        "text": "It's made of ad, meaning to or of,"
      },
      {
        "start": 65.3,
        "duration": 3.6,
        "text": "and cumu, from Latin\ncumulus, meaning a heap."
      },
      {
        "start": 68.9,
        "duration": 1.8,
        "text": "It does that assimilation trick"
      },
      {
        "start": 70.7,
        "duration": 2.8,
        "text": "where the D in ad becomes another C"
      },
      {
        "start": 73.5,
        "duration": 2.1,
        "text": "to match up with the C in cumul, right?"
      },
      {
        "start": 75.6,
        "duration": 3.4,
        "text": "Instead of addcumulate, we say accumulate."
      },
      {
        "start": 79.0,
        "duration": 2.0,
        "text": "Not a ton of other related words here."
      },
      {
        "start": 81.0,
        "duration": 2.7,
        "text": "Maybe you've seen the term cumulus cloud,"
      },
      {
        "start": 83.7,
        "duration": 3.7,
        "text": "which is a big heaped\nup, fluffy-looking cloud."
      },
      {
        "start": 87.4,
        "duration": 2.6,
        "text": "Vast comes to us from Latin vastus,"
      },
      {
        "start": 90.0,
        "duration": 2.3,
        "text": "meaning empty or desolate."
      },
      {
        "start": 92.3,
        "duration": 2.0,
        "text": "We use it just to mean very large,"
      },
